                                                                  9031 1451
  2) Two-component exciton model/23/                              9031 1451
    * Global parametrization of Koning-Duijvestijn/24/            9031 1451
      was used.                                                   9031 1451
    * Gamma emission channel/25/ was added to simulate direct     9031 1451
      and semi-direct capture reaction.                           9031 1451
                                                                  9031 1451
  3) Hauser-Feshbach statistical model                            9031 1451
    * Moldauer width fluctuation correction/26/ was included.     9031 1451
    * Neutron, gamma and fission decay channel were included.     9031 1451
    * Transmission coefficients of neutrons were taken from       9031 1451
      coupled channel calculation in Table 1.                     9031 1451
    * The level scheme of the target is shown in Table 2.         9031 1451
    * Level density formula of constant temperature and Fermi-gas 9031 1451
      model were used with shell energy correction and collective 9031 1451
      enhancement factor. Parameters are shown in Table 3.        9031 1451
    * Fission channel:                                            9031 1451
      Double humped fission barriers were assumed.                9031 1451
      Fission barrier penetrabilities were calculated with        9031 1451
      Hill-Wheler formula/27/. Fission barrier parameters were    9031 1451
      shown in Table 4. Transition state model was used and       9031 1451
      continuum levels are assumed above the saddles. The level   9031 1451
      density parameters for inner and outer saddles are shown in 9031 1451
      Tables 5 and 6, respectively.                               9031 1451
    * Gamma-ray strength function of Kopecky et al/28/,/29/       9031 1451
      was used. The prameters are shown in Table 7.               9031 1451
